The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at the 37th Annual National Peace Officers' Memorial Service during National Police Week. He expressed gratitude for the courageous men and women of law enforcement and honored the families of fallen officers. Pence highlighted the actions taken by President Donald Trump to support law enforcement, including providing additional tools, funding, and equipment. He acknowledged the hardships and challenges faced by law enforcement officers and paid tribute to the 28 officers who lost their lives this year. Pence emphasized the importance of law enforcement in ensuring the safety and security of communities and praised their selfless dedication. He assured that the Trump administration will continue to support and fight for law enforcement. Pence concluded by expressing condolences to the families of the fallen and offering blessings to those who protect and serve.